President Muhammadu Buhari has directed Ministries, Departments and Agencies, to submit details of their 2018 budget estimates to the appropriate committees of the National Assembly not later than Friday March 23, 2018. The Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) Mr Boss Gida Mustapha conveyed the directives in a circular dated 19 March 2018 to all MDAs with Ref. No. SGF/OP/1/S.3/XII. The circular titled “Submission of Details of the 2018 Budget Estimates by Federal Government owned Agencies, Parastatals and Corporations to the National Assembly” also directed that the agencies comply with the provisions of the law and honour invitation to defend their estimates as scheduled.